@@aOvergrowth@@N is the core mechanic of the Druid class.

Druid spells cost @@eHP@@N instead of mana. Each cast adds Overgrowth stacks
based on the spell's growth value, up to a maximum of 100.

@@WEffects of Overgrowth:@@N
 - @@eCost increase@@N: HP cost rises by 2% per stack
 - @@aDamage bonus@@N: Druid spell damage increases by 3% per stack
 - @@WDecay@@N: Out of combat, decays by 1/tick (2/tick if resting/sleeping)
 - @@eDeath protection@@N: If a spell would kill you, HP is set to 1 and
   Overgrowth is maxed at 100
 - @@WDeath reset@@N: Overgrowth resets to 0 on death

The Druid walks a razor's edge between destruction and self-destruction.
